10px;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-top=
: 30px; margin-bottom: 0;">Engine No. 1=E2=80=99s economics</h2><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">We talked a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2F=
ydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjYvZXh4b24taGFzLWEtdG91Z2gtZ3JlZW4tYWN0aXZpc3Q/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cBc6f1b84d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;"> couple</a> of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9=
uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjcvZXh4b24tbG9zdC1hLWNsaW1hdGUtcHJveHktZmlnaHQ/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1a89aafb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> times</a> last week about the plucky and successful=
=C2=A0activist campaign that hedge fund Engine No. 1 LLC waged against Exxo=
n Mobil Corp. I wrote on Thursday:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">Actually it=E2=80=99s a little mysterious to me what=E2=80=99s in it fo=
r Engine No. 1? As we discussed yesterday, it owns 917,400 shares of Exxon =
stock and spent about $30 million on the proxy fight. It bought that stock =
in mid-November and early December, when Exxon was trading at around $37 or=
 $38 per share; it closed yesterday at $58.94. Figure the fund is up about =
$21 per share, and has collected another $1.74 per share in dividends, and =
you get a gross profit of maybe $21 million; after proxy-fight expenses tha=
t=E2=80=99s a loss of $9 million. Perhaps now that its nominees are on the =
board, Exxon will change strategy and add a lot of long-term value and make=
 Engine No. 1 rich. Or perhaps there are some other economics that I=E2=80=
=99m missing. But it=E2=80=99s not obvious to me how this trade =E2=80=94 s=
pend $35 million on stock and $30 million on a proxy fight =E2=80=94 makes =
a lot of economic sense. Maybe they just did it for the good of the planet.=
</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well! About a hundred of you =
emailed me to say that it=E2=80=99s obvious what=E2=80=99s in it for Engine=
 No. 1: publicity. This is a hedge fund that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc3N3aXJl=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2hvbWUvMjAyMDEyMDEwMDU3MDMvZW4vRW5naW5lLU5vLi0xLUxhdW5jaGVzLXR=
vLUJyaW5nLUFjdGl2ZS1Pd25lcnNoaXAtYW5kLUltcGFjdC1Ecml2ZW4tU3RyYXRlZ3ktdG8tSW=
52ZXN0aW5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfa530de9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">launched six months ago</a>; it runs a =
small fund and doesn=E2=80=99t have much of a track record. Now it is=C2=A0=
The Little Engine That Took Down Exxon. It has=C2=A0gone from nothing to be=
ing a daring successful activist, <em>and=C2=A0</em>an activist with a halo=
 of environmental virtue. It can fundraise off of that forever, attract lot=
s of money, collect lots of fees, etc. The $30 million of proxy expenses ar=
e an investment to make millions more in management fees.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">A related benefit is what any activist fund gets from a succ=
essful proxy fight: The=C2=A0<em>next=C2=A0</em>company they go after will =
be intimidated by their Exxon victory,=C2=A0and will try to settle by givin=
g them board seats. You spend $30 million on one proxy fight so you don=E2=
=80=99t have to spend any money on five more. You show up at a meeting with=
 the next company=E2=80=99s CEO, you put Exxon=E2=80=99s severed head on th=
e table, you say =E2=80=9Cboard seats, now,=E2=80=9D and you get them witho=
ut a fight.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fine! That=E2=80=99s all =
fair enough. One reader pointed out another, more technical but also quite =
important answer: It is customary for activist hedge funds that=C2=A0<em>wi=
n=C2=A0</em>their proxy fights to be=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY29tcGxpYW5jZXdlZWs=
uY29tL2FjdGl2aXN0cy1ub3ctcHVzaC1wcm94eS1maWdodC1wYXliYWNrcy82NjEyLmFydGljbG=
U/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB63fdfbe9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">reimbursed by the company</a>.[1] So, because it=
 won, Engine No. 1 probably spent $30 million of Exxon=E2=80=99s money on t=
he proxy fight, not its own. That probably helps. It took a big=C2=A0<em>ri=
sk=C2=A0</em>here: If it had lost the proxy fight, it would be out $30 mill=
ion and wouldn=E2=80=99t have all the fundraising benefit of having taken d=
own Exxon. But because it won, the economics actually look pretty good.</p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vYnV=
zaW5lc3MvZW5lcmd5L3N0YXRlLXN0cmVldC1iYWNrZWQtdHdvLWFjdGl2aXN0LWhlZGdlLWZ1bm=
Qtbm9taW5lZXMtZXh4b24tYm9hcmQtMjAyMS0wNS0yNy8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB835d=
5123" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the =
Exxon proxy fight</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Asset ma=
nager State Street Corp voted for two of the four candidates put forward by=
 activist hedge fund Engine No. 1 for Exxon Mobil's board, a spokesman for =
the Boston firm said late on Thursday.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Stat=
e Street was Exxon's third-largest investor according to its proxy statemen=
t. Late on Wednesday Exxon's largest investor Vanguard Group said it also b=
acked two dissident nominees, details that fleshed out how Engine No. 1 was=
 able to capture at least two board seats at the biggest U.S. oil producer.=
</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When we talked about the prox=
y fight last week, I used BlackRock Inc. as an example of a big index-y Exx=
on shareholder that wants companies to care more about climate change and s=
upported Engine No. 1=E2=80=99s push for a more renewables-focused Exxon. B=
lackRock is Exxon=E2=80=99s second-biggest shareholder, loves to <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDEtMTQvYmxhY2tyb2NrLWh=
hcy1ncmVlbi1wbGFucw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB77a1f130" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> talk=C2=A0about sustainabilit=
y</a>, and released a =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxhY2tyb2NrLmNvbS9jb3Jwb3JhdG=
UvbGl0ZXJhdHVyZS9wcmVzcy1yZWxlYXNlL2Jsay12b3RlLWJ1bGxldGluLWV4eG9uLW1heS0yM=
DIxLnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB996bd8f5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">vote bulletin</a>=E2=80=9D last week say=
ing=C2=A0that it would be voting for three of Engine No. 1=E2=80=99s direct=
or candidates; it was the most obvious example. But the other two =E2=80=9C=
Big Three=E2=80=9D index-y shareholders also voted for change. The lesson h=
ere is that if you are a small activist looking to run a proxy fight to pus=
h a big company in an environmental/social/governance direction, you might =
be able to pick up some big allies.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjkvZXh4b24tbW9iaWwt=
cy1sYXN0LWRpdGNoLWF0dGVtcHQtdG8tc3RhdmUtb2ZmLWEtY2xpbWF0ZS1jb3Vw/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBd301705f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> Also</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In th=
e hours leading up to this week=E2=80=99s annual shareholders meeting, Exxo=
n went to extraordinary lengths to head off the threat from a campaign abou=
t which it had been largely dismissive months earlier.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">Exxon telephoned investors the morning of the ballot -- and eve=
n during an unscheduled, hour-long pause during the virtual meeting -- aski=
ng them to reconsider their votes, according to several of those who receiv=
ed calls. Some said they found the last-ditch outreach and halt to the meet=
ing unorthodox and troubling.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt w=
as a very unusual annual general meeting,=E2=80=9D said Aeisha Mastagni, a =
fund manager at the California State Teachers=E2=80=99 Retirement System, a=
 major Exxon investor that backed the activist campaign from the beginning.=
 =E2=80=9CIt didn=E2=80=99t feel good as an investor.=E2=80=9D</p></blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think the basic reading here is that at =
a giant public company like Exxon, the managers and board of directors sort=
 of assume that they get to decide who can be on the board, and that shareh=
olders are not really supposed to interfere. Technically this assumption is=
 wrong, and at Exxon last week it did not work out, but you can see why Exx=
on found it so surprising.</p><h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: =
&quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px=
; font-size: 20px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; p=
adding-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 0;">AMC</h2><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGV=
zLzIwMjEtMDYtMDEvYW1jLWV4dGVuZHMtcmFsbHktYWZ0ZXItMjMwLTUtbWlsbGlvbi1zdG9jay=
1zYWxlLXRvLW11ZHJpY2s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe59c85e8" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a great trade here</a>:</p>=
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. ga=
ined Tuesday, extending last week=E2=80=99s rally, after raising $230.5 mil=
lion with a stock sale to Mudrick Capital Management as the movie-theater o=
perator pledged to =E2=80=9Cgo on offense=E2=80=9D with acquisitions.</p><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The agreement with New York-based Mudrick is for=
 8.5 million shares of common stock at $27.12 apiece, 3.8% more than Friday=
=E2=80=99s closing price, AMC said Tuesday in a statement. The company, now=
 an icon among retail traders, jumped as much as 23% to $32 at the open in =
New York trading. It traded at $29.98 at 9:35 a.m.</p><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">The latest equity sale with Mudrick =E2=80=9Csounds expensive=E2=80=
=9D with debt and equity indicating an enterprise value of over $16 billion=
, Michael Pachter of Wedbush said in an email to Bloomberg. If it returns t=
o pre-Covid levels, AMC could optimistically reach around $1 billion in ear=
nings after adjustments. The highest attained in the past is $929 million i=
n 2018, he said. =E2=80=9CMudrick must know something I don=E2=80=99t.=E2=
=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s a thing =
Mudrick knows:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mudrick=E2=80=99=
s stock purchase comes with the caveat that the shares be =E2=80=9Cfreely-t=
radeable=E2=80=9D, meaning the firm could sell the shares at any point or i=
n any size it chooses. That would provide Mudrick with 8.5 million shares t=
hat could be sold as soon as today.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">Here are the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MT=
E1NzkvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMDc0NTg0L3RtMjExNzk4NmQzX2RlZmExNGEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cB5c939302" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">press release</a>=C2=A0and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlc=
y9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTE1NzkvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMDc0NTIwL3RtMjExNzk4Ni0xXzQyNGI3=
Lmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB14934b90" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">the prospectus</a> for Mudrick=E2=80=99s p=
otential sales. (Don=E2=80=99t miss the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDMtMjQvbmZsLWZ1dHVyZXMtYmV0dGluZy15b3UtY2FuLXQt=
dHJhZGUtb24tcHJvLWZvb3RiYWxsLW9kZHM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4baa4cdd" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> GameStop</a>-=
style <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269=
579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTE1NzkvMDAwMTE=
wNDY1OTIxMDc0NTIwL3RtMjExNzk4Ni0xXzQyNGI3Lmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC14=
934b90" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000=
000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bot=
tom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">ri=
sk factors</a>, which include: =E2=80=9CWithin the last seven business days=
, the market price of our Class A common stock has fluctuated from an intra=
-day low of 12.05 on May 21, 2021 to $36.72 on May 28, 2021, and we have ma=
de no disclosure regarding a change to our underlying business during that =
period.=E2=80=9D) I have no idea what Mudrick is actually doing; all I am s=
aying is that this is not a trade that ought to work under traditional theo=
ries, but it=E2=80=99s very much a trade that works now:</p><ol style=3D"li=
st-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A meme stock closes on Friday at $26.12 per share,=
 up 116% on the week on no particular news (but with <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24023110.269579/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjcvYW1jLXMtZm91ci1kYXktc3VyZ2Utc2x=
hcHMtc2hvcnQtc2VsbGVycy13aXRoLTEtMy1iaWxsaW9uLWxvc3M/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB8f9c0ab7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">  lots of talk about short squeezes</a>).</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bot=
tom: 5px;">You buy stock from the company over the holiday weekend=C2=A0<em=
>at a premium</em>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You announce i=
t on Tuesday morning.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Everyone say=
s =E2=80=9Coh wow good news for that meme stock, guess the wild rally is go=
ing to continue.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So it do=
es.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You sell the stock=C2=A0into t=
he enormous volume and rising prices on Tuesday morning.</li></ol><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Like imagine the negotiations over the price. It is tr=
aditional, when one investor buys a big chunk of stock from a company, for =
the investor to get a bit of a discount. Here, though, the premium helps Mu=
drick: It makes the stock sale less dilutive, signals confidence in the sto=
ck, feels like a win. So the stock goes up even more and, if Mudrick=C2=A0<=
em>does=C2=A0</em>want to sell immediately, it can do so at a profit.=C2=A0=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I wonder if banks are pitching AMC on boug=
ht-deal stock offerings. I wonder what price they=E2=80=99re pitching. The =
traditional answer, for a volatile and meme-y stock, would be that you=E2=
=80=99d want a healthy discount to account for all of the risk you take in =
reselling the stock: =E2=80=9CWe are confident in AMC and so can offer you =
a bought deal at a tight discount, down just 5% from yesterday=E2=80=99s cl=
ose.=E2=80=9D But the right answer is actually a healthy premium.</p>
